For the following to work you have to first setup a Developer version of LaueG on your PC.

======== Building a new installation *.exe file for LaueG ========

In the "My Stuff" menu of LaueG (Developer mode), run:
	"Save Source"
	"Create Release Code"
	"Generate Build Folder"

Run "WindowsInstall.iss" in C:\DevApps\LaueG\_Release\ which will start Inno Setup
	Use "Build"->"Compile"

The setup file LaueG_setup_<date>.exe is created in C:\DevApps\LaueG\_Release\Installs\
